Global Slip Agent Market Insights
Slip Agent Market size was valued at USD 1.75 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.95 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Slip Agent Market Overview
The global slip agent market was valued at approximately USD 900 million in 2024, with expectations of steady growth driven by increasing demand across various industries such as packaging, automotive, and consumer goods. The market is forecasted to grow at a CAGR of 4.2% from 2025 to 2030. Slip agents are chemicals used in plastics to reduce friction and enhance processing characteristics, resulting in smoother surfaces and improved product quality. The rise in demand for high-performance materials, coupled with the growing need for sustainability, is expected to influence market trends positively. Additionally, the shift towards bio-based slip agents is projected to create new growth opportunities in the coming years. Global trends toward efficient manufacturing and eco-friendly products further drive market expansion.

